<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="437" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1064</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-12T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 12, 1917—5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your February 10, 10 p.m. and February 11, 11 p.m. Department has made
                            public this afternoon statement transmitted in its February 10, 7 p.m.
                            You are authorized to give it to Cuban press. If President Menocal and
                            Zayas have no objections you are authorized to send military attaché to
                            Santa Clara to observe elections but to give no counsel and take no
                            active part in supervision.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>